## Pipelines — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage CI/CD pipelines for this project. All requests require a personal access token passed in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### List Pipelines

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `status` (optional) — Filter by pipeline status: `created`, `pending`, `running`, `success`, `failed`, `canceled`, `skipped`, `manual`, `scheduled`
- `ref` (optional) — Filter by branch or tag name
- `sha` (optional) — Filter by commit SHA
- `page` (optional) — Page number (default: `1`)
- `per_page` (optional) — Items per page, max `100` (default: `20`)

**Response fields per pipeline:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | Pipeline ID |
| `iid` | Pipeline internal ID scoped to the project |
| `project_id` | Project ID |
| `sha` | Commit SHA |
| `ref` | Branch or tag name |
| `status` | Pipeline status |
| `source` | How the pipeline was triggered (e.g. `push`, `api`, `schedule`) |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp |
| `started_at` | Start timestamp |
| `finished_at` | Finish timestamp |
| `duration` | Duration in seconds |
| `web_url` | URL to view the pipeline in the browser |

**Pagination headers returned:**

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `X-Total` | Total number of pipelines |
| `X-Total-Pages` | Total number of pages |
| `X-Page` | Current page |
| `X-Per-Page` | Items per page |
| `X-Next-Page` | Next page number (empty if on last page) |
| `X-Prev-Page` | Previous page number (empty if on first page) |

---

### Get a Single Pipeline

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines/:id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Pipeline ID
- Returns `404 Not Found` if the pipeline does not exist

---

### Create a Pipeline

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"ref": "main"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `ref` (required) — Branch or tag name to run the pipeline on
- `variables` (optional) — Array of `{key, value}` objects to pass as pipeline variables

Returns `201 Created` with the pipeline object on success.
Returns `400 Bad Request` if `ref` is missing or invalid.

---

### Retry a Pipeline

Retries all failed or canceled jobs in the pipeline.

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines/:id/retry" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Pipeline ID
- Returns `200 OK` with the pipeline object on success
- Returns `400 Bad Request` if there are no retryable jobs

---

### Cancel a Pipeline

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines/:id/cancel" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Pipeline ID
- Returns `200 OK` with the pipeline object on success
- Returns `400 Bad Request` if the pipeline is not cancelable

---

### Delete a Pipeline

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/pipelines/:id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:id` — Pipeline ID
- Returns `204 No Content` on success
- Returns `403 Forbidden` if you do not have permission
